      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Effective latency management starts with defining clear metrics. For FLUX.1 schnell, focus on time-to-first-token (TTFT), total inference time, and end-to-end API response latency. TTFT measures the delay from request initiation to the first output token, critical for streaming applications. Total inference time covers the full model processing, while end-to-end latency includes network overhead. Monitor these metrics using tools like Prometheus or OpenTelemetry to establish baselines and identify bottlenecks."
          }
        ]
